The paper proposes a new scheme for modelling the behavior of neurons, which is likely to fall under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). The specific application of the proposed method is in recreating the behavior of neurons in the human auditory and visual system, which suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions improvements in learning speed and performance, which could be related to machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses a reduction in memory for storing network parameters, which could be relevant to systems and control (cs.SD).
